354. ipsus, i.e. erus, Mega- dorus, ‘the governor.' This use of ipsus is probably an imi- tation of the G,reek αὑτός, for thus disciples and slaves called their masters: e. g. αὐτὸς ἔφα ipse dixit, where αὐτός means the all-revereri master Pythag- oras.
